ZH: 我想认识一位新朋友。
EN: I want to make friends with a new acquaintance.

ZH: 他们在大学认识的。
EN: They met at college.

ZH: 你认识那个人吗？
EN: Do you know that person?

ZH: 我们是通过工作认识的。
EN: We met through work.

ZH: 这是我第一次见到他，我们还不够熟。
EN: This is the first time I've seen him, we're not close yet.

ZH: 我在派对上认识的她。
EN: I met her at a party.

ZH: 这个网站帮助你认识新朋友。
EN: This website helps you meet new friends.

ZH: 他们两个是以前的同学，所以很认识。
EN: They are former classmates, so they know each other well.

ZH: 你会认识那个著名的歌手吗？
EN: Will you recognize that famous singer?

ZH: 你一定能够认识他，他很容易辨认。
EN: You will definitely recognize him, he is easy to identify.

ZH: 他很容易认识，因为他长得很特别。
EN: He is easy to recognize because he looks distinctive.

ZH: 我们在旅行途中认识了许多有趣的人。
EN: We met many interesting people during our travels.

ZH: 我很高兴认识你。
EN: I am glad to meet you.

ZH: 他是我最好的朋友，我们认识了十年。
EN: He is my best friend, we have known each other for ten years.

ZH: 我父母是在大学认识的。
EN: My parents met in college.

ZH: 我常常在这个游乐园认识一些有趣的人。
EN: I often meet interesting people at this amusement park.

ZH: 我们之前只是网上认识，后来见面后变成了好朋友。
EN: We only knew each other online before, but after meeting in person, we became good friends.

ZH: 我们需要尽快认识对方的家庭。
EN: We need to get to know each other's families as soon as possible.

ZH: 通过这个社交平台，我认识了很多优秀的人。
EN: Through this social platform, I have met many outstanding people.

ZH: 认识新的文化可以拓宽我们的视野。
EN: Getting to know new cultures can broaden our horizons.
